

Node

				1. Node JS run JS
				2. Node JS does not support browser based libraries
				3. Node JS has some inbuilt global variables/functions
				4. Node JS runs js by using v8 engine
				5. Most of node js platform is written in c++
				6. Node JS supports libraries to deal with http, fs, os, network protocals
				,rdbms...
				7. Node JS provides lot of inbuilt modules(libraries)
				8. Node js is non blocking and asynchronous in nature
				
NPM

				1.it is a package management utility
				2.node app is a node package
				3. by using npm we manage dependencies, app stucture and other development 
				related activities(testing,build,linting,...)
				
				